sub_topic: The self-similarity of the Vicsek fractal.
message_1: What is the Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal? Round your answer to two decimal places.
message_2:
The Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal can be calculated using the formula:

D = log(N) / log(s)

where D is the Hausdorff dimension, N is the number of self-similar pieces, and s is the scaling factor.

For the Vicsek fractal, N = 5 (since there are 5 smaller copies of the fractal in each iteration) and s = 3 (since each side of the square is divided into 3 equal parts).

So, the Hausdorff dimension is:

D = log(5) / log(3)

Rounded to two decimal places, the Hausdorff dimension of the Vicsek fractal is 1.47.
